description: Numbers k that are not prime powers (i.e., not in A000961) such that A328925(k) > 1; numbers k such that if we write k = Product_{i=1..t} p_i^e_i , then t > 1, and lcm_{1<=i,j<=t, i!=j} ord(p_i,p_j^e_j) < A002322(k), where ord(a,r) is the multiplicative order of a modulo r, and A002322 is the Carmichael lambda (usually written as psi).
